      • labelMatches

        public boolean labelMatches(Nonterminal nonterminal)
        Description copied from interface: Nonterminal
        checks whether the pure labels of the nonterminal (i.e. without stack or other additional information) matches. E.g. B[ssZ], B[sX], B[s()], B[abc] would all be considered to have matching label
        However, this does'nt match for nonterminals of different type, e.g. B and B[Z] should not match.
        Specified by:
        labelMatches in interface Nonterminal
        Parameters:
        nonterminal - the nonterminal to check against
        Returns:
        true if the label of this and nonterminl match.
